message_1:
Here is a problem: 

Let S be the set of all possible computer programs that print an integer on the screen. Suppose we have a computer program which takes a positive integer input n and outputs 2n. Is this program a member of set S?
message_2: Yes, this program is a member of set S. The program takes a positive integer input n and outputs 2n, which is also an integer. Since the program prints an integer on the screen, it belongs to the set S of all possible computer programs that print an integer on the screen.
